CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 29, 1965, pg. 9 reads: "Stoop N' Bend - Flowers, aprons, jewelry and a variety of other articles were on sale at the Stoop 'n' Bend Garden Club booth. Several of the Stoop 'n' Bend members are seen showing some of their wares to Mrs. John McKee (back to camera, in dark dress).  Members in and out of the booth included Mmes. Henry Patterson, president; William Mitchell, financial secretary; Lloyd Johnson, treasurer; Jesse Bolden; Harold Stoner, chairman; Warren Tucker, co-chairman; Ulysses Williams, Andrew Vaughn and S. Adams, co-chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of Stoop 'N Bend club members and guests, including Mrs. John McKee wearing dark polka dot dress, Mrs. Henry Patterson, Mrs. William Mitchell, Mrs. Lloyd Johnson, Mrs. Jesse Bolden, Mrs. Harold Stoner, Mrs. Warren Tucker, Mrs. Ulysses Williams, Mrs. Andrew Vaughn, and Mrs. S. Adams, gathered at Club booth, during the Garden Market held at the Garden Center, Shady Avenue
